<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Echthrus</taxonomicName>
is placed in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="tribe" tribe="Cryptini">Cryptini</taxonomicName>
, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenne, N. M." journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="442 - 473" title="Direct optimization and multiple alignment of 28 S D 2 - D 3 rDNA sequences: problems with indels on the way to a molecular phylogeny of the cryptine ichneumon wasps (Insecta: Hymenoptera)" volume="22" year="2006">Laurenne et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, rather than in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="tribe" tribe="Hemigastrini">Hemigastrini</taxonomicName>
, where it was placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. K." journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 537" title="The genera of Ichneumonidae, Part 2" volume="12" year="1970">Townes (1970)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. K." journalOrPublisher="United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 676" title="Ichneumon-flies of American north of Mexico: 2 Subfamily Ephialtinae, Xoridinae, Acaenitinae" volume="216" year="1960">Townes and Townes (1960)</bibRefCitation>
had previously placed 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Echthrus</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="tribe" tribe="Cryptini">Cryptini</taxonomicName>
based on similarities to the genera that 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. K." journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 537" title="The genera of Ichneumonidae, Part 2" volume="12" year="1970">Townes (1970)</bibRefCitation>
classified as the subtribe 
<taxonomicName genus="Gabuniina" lsidName="Gabuniina" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Gabuniina">Gabuniina</taxonomicName>
. The molecular results of 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenne, N. M." journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="442 - 473" title="Direct optimization and multiple alignment of 28 S D 2 - D 3 rDNA sequences: problems with indels on the way to a molecular phylogeny of the cryptine ichneumon wasps (Insecta: Hymenoptera)" volume="22" year="2006">Laurenne et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
support this interpretation, in agreement with 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. K." journalOrPublisher="United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 602" title="Ichneumon-flies of America north of Mexico: 3. Subfamily Gelinae, tribe Mesostenini" volume="216" year="1962">Townes and Townes (1962)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
